definitions.definition: A set or group with ten elements .
examples: We divided the chocolates into tens to hand out to Hallowe'en visitors.

definitions.definition: An inexact quantity, typically understood to be between 20 and 100 .
examples: Our houses are tens of meters apart, so we don't have to worry about noise from our neighbours.

definitions.definition: A card in a given suit with a value of ten.
A denomination of currency , such as a banknote , with a value of ten units .
examples: Can you give me two tens for this twenty?

definitions.definition: A perfect specimen , ( particularly ) a physically attractive person .
The act of rowing ten strokes flat out .

main_definition: A set or group with ten elements .
secondary_definitions: ( in the plural ) An inexact quantity, typically understood to be between 20 and 100 .
( countable , card games ) A card in a given suit with a value of ten.
( countable ) A denomination of currency , such as a banknote , with a value of ten units .
( countable , US , slang ) A perfect specimen , ( particularly ) a physically attractive person .
( countable , US , slang ) A high level of intensity.
( countable , rowing ) The act of rowing ten strokes flat out .
